.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-PREPARE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.16" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-prepare \- Prepare imported and customized runtime images
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose prepare [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Import base images and build prepared runtime artifacts on the submission host. This is the login\-node image preparation phase reused later by submit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read. Default: compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--enroot\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the enroot executable. Default: enroot.
.TP
\fB--keep\-failed\-prep\fR
Keep failed preparation state on disk for later inspection.
.TP
\fB--force\fR
Refresh imported and prepared artifacts even when cache entries exist.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose prepare \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose prepare \-f compose.yaml \-\-force
hpc\-compose prepare \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
